201 During fiscal year 2027, and notwithstanding any provision of law to the
202 contrary, the Chief Justice of the Supreme Court of Alabama may transfer up to
203 $12,000,000 from local discretionary funds managed by circuit clerks and
204 circuit and district judges, including Circuit Clerk’s Funds, Circuit Clerk’s
205 Judicial Administration Funds, and Presiding Judge Judicial Administration
206 Funds. The Chief Justice may require each circuit clerk or judge responsible
207 for the administration of such funds to remit to the Administrative Office of
208 Courts a graduated proportional share of the available balances of such funds.
209 The Chief Justice may establish the schedule, methodology, and date used to
210 determine the balances subject to transfer, and any amounts expended after
211 that date that would otherwise reduce the balances subject to transfer may be
212 included in calculating the required remittance. Any funds transferred
213 pursuant to this section shall be remitted to the Administrative Director of
214 Courts for deposit into the State Judicial Administration Fund and used for
215 the operational expenses of the Unified Judicial System in fiscal year 2027.
