323 other expenditures herein authorized, such sums as are or may be necessary to
324 purchase the alcoholic beverages which are essential to maintain adequate stocks and
325 inventory for an economic and successful sales operation. In addition to the above
326 appropriation, it is further provided that, in the event any county or municipality
327 of the state shall, during the fiscal period covered by this appropriation by proper
328 referendum, authorize the legal sale of malt and brewed beverages within such county
329 or municipality there is further appropriated, in addition to the amount herein set
330 out, an amount comparable to that expended during the prior fiscal year for beer and
331 license tax supervision within counties or municipalities of similar size and
332 population. Provided further, that the amount appropriated herein shall be reduced
333 in like manner in the event any county or municipality wherein malt and brewed
334 beverages are now authorized by law to be sold shall, during the fiscal period
335 covered by this appropriation by proper referendum, declare unlawful the sale in
336 such county or municipality of such malt or brewed beverages. Notwithstanding any
337 other laws to the contrary, all revenue generated from bailment fees shall remain
338 with the Board to be used for its operations.
