1394 To award matching grants for ambulances for emergency medical services operating in rural
1395 counties. The Office may consider requests for matching grants to buy an ambulance,
1396 rapid-response vehicle, or cardiac monitor or other durable medical equipment to be placed in
1397 an ambulance or rapid-response vehicle, from a county, city, hospital, or ambulance service.
1398 The Office may award a grant equal to no more than 75 percent of the cost of the ambulance,
1399 rapid-response vehicle, or equipment, the percentage depending on the financial resources of
1400 the applicant and the need for the vehicle or equipment as judged by officials with the state’s
1401 regional emergency medical services offices. Preference shall be given to grants for an
1402 ambulance or rapid-response vehicle that would be based in a county with two or fewer
1403 ambulances. The Office shall file a report with the Chairs of the Senate Committee on Finance
1404 and Taxation-General Fund and the House Ways and Means-General Fund, the Legislative Fiscal
1405 Officer and the Finance Director by October 15, 2027, on how the money was spent in fiscal year
1406 2027. The report shall list each vehicle or piece of equipment purchased or planned to be
1407 purchased with a grant from the Office, the government or other organization that bought or
1408 planned to buy the vehicle or equipment, the total cost of the vehicle or equipment and the
1409 grant amount awarded to help pay for it, and why the Office awarded each grant.
