1859 The Medicaid Agency will reimburse the Department of Public Health for
1860 actual costs (in compliance with OMB Circular A-87 and Centers for Medicare
1861 and Medicaid Services guidelines) for services provided. The Department of
1862 Public Health shall transfer to the Medicaid Agency the state funds
1863 attributable to the difference between their costs and Medicaid's routine
1864 reimbursement fee. The Medicaid Agency shall make every effort to maintain
1865 level funding for the adult prosthetic and orthotic program in fiscal year
1866 2027. Any requirements for prior authorization of antipsychotic drugs will be
1867 for the limited purpose of managing off-label utilization. The Medicaid Agency
1868 shall make every effort to provide access for medications prescribed in
1869 accordance with FDA approved indications for mental illness and HIV/AIDS. The
1870 Alabama Medicaid Agency shall not pay for a generic drug that is more
1871 expensive than its brand name drug, net of rebates. The Alabama Medicaid
1872 Agency shall continue to fund and support the PACE program in accordance with
1873 written agreements.
