2567 The amounts hereinabove appropriated for the cost of maintenance and operations of
2568 the Department of Revenue are in lieu of any other statutory provisions for the
2569 payment of the cost of operating said Department for collections of the taxes as
2570 authorized by law. Provided, however, in addition to the amount hereinabove
2571 appropriated, there is hereby appropriated to the Department of Revenue all sums
2572 allowed the Department of Revenue by acts of the Legislature as a charge for the
2573 collection of taxes or licenses. The Revenue Department shall not be limited in any
2574 way whatsoever in its ability to utilize or spend its full appropriation and all
2575 sums allowed to the Department of Revenue by acts of the Legislature as a charge for
2576 the collection of taxes or licenses. It is the intent of the Legislature that the
2577 Department of Revenue utilize the appropriations made to it in this act to: (1)
2578 significantly reduce the amount of delinquent taxes owed to the state; (2) employ
2579 sufficient examiners and audit personnel to ensure that taxes owed to the state are
2580 collected accurately and timely; and (3) update its personal computers and related
2581 equipment to become more efficient in the collection of taxes owed to the state.
2582 During Fiscal Year 2027, the Department shall report semi-annually to the Chairs of
2583 the House Ways and Means-General Fund Committee, Senate Finance and Taxation-General
2584 Fund Committee, and the Legislative Fiscal Officer on all actions taken by the
2585 Department in furtherance of these goals. The reports shall include, but not be
2586 limited to: (1) the number and amount of delinquent taxes collected during the
2587 quarter and the number and amounts of delinquent taxes outstanding as of the end of
2588 the quarter; (2) the number of additional examiners and audit personnel employed
2589 during the quarter (not including examiners and audit personnel employed to replace
2590 personnel that retire or otherwise leave state service); and (3) the number of new
2591 personal computers and related equipment put into use during the quarter.
