2639 The Alabama SenioRx program shall provide assistance obtaining prescription
2640 medications and shall be expanded to allow comprehensive benefits screening
2641 and application assistance through an Area Agency on Aging designated by the
2642 Department as an Aging and Disability Resource Center (ADRC). It is the intent
2643 of the Legislature that applicants apply through local Area Agencies on Aging
2644 and their provider networks to ensure services are maximized and that
2645 paperwork and inconvenience to the clients are minimized to receive access to
2646 local and public benefits and prescription assistance. The Department of
2647 Senior Services shall report semi-annually to the Chairs of the House Ways and
2648 Means-General Fund Committee and the Senate Finance and Taxation-General Fund
2649 Committee, the Governor, the Director of Finance, and the Legislative Fiscal
2650 Officer. The reports shall include the number of clients served by an ADRC,
2651 the number of unduplicated SenioRx participants, the number of prescriptions
2652 filled, and the estimated value of the drugs provided.
