2798 There is hereby appropriated for payment of the principal of and the interest
2799 on all bonds heretofore or hereafter issued for public highways and bridge
2800 purposes, or either, by the State of Alabama, Alabama Federal Aid Highway
2801 Finance Authority, Alabama Highway Finance Corporation, Alabama Industrial
2802 Access Road and Bridge Corporation, or Alabama Highway Authority a total of
2803 $192,993,061 or so much thereof as may be necessary for payment of said
2804 principal and interest at their respective maturities, of the revenues pledged
2805 for such payment. There is also hereby appropriated an amount not to exceed
2806 $25,000,000 as an annual contribution to the Alabama Transportation
2807 Infrastructure Bank, if needed, for payment of debt service. The Director of
2808 Transportation, with the consent of the Governor and the Director of Finance,
2809 shall have the authority to transfer any appropriation or any portion thereof
2810 between and among subdivisions (a), (b) and (c) of this section whenever such
2811 transfer shall be necessary to assure maximum utilization of federal matching
2812 funds which shall become available. In the event that there shall not be
2813 sufficient funds available for payment of all appropriations hereinabove made,
2814 the following provisions shall be applicable. In the event of such
2815 insufficiency in respect of said revenues accruing to the Department of
2816 Transportation: (1) the appropriation made for Debt Service in subdivisions
2817 (a) and (b) hereof shall be paid in full, and (2) the appropriations from the
2818 revenues accruing to the Department of Transportation that are herein made for
2819 the purposes referred to in subdivisions (a), (b) and (c) except for Debt
2820 Service, hereof shall be allocated among the purposes referred to in said
2821 subdivisions in such order and with such priorities as the Director of the
2822 Department of Transportation shall from time to time direct. The funds
2823 appropriated in subdivisions (a) and (c) hereof, for the matching federal
2824 funds, shall not revert at the end of the fiscal year for which such
2825 appropriations are made but shall remain available for the purposes for which
2826 such appropriations were made. In addition to all appropriations hereinabove
2827 made, there is hereby appropriated to the Department of Transportation all
2828 federal funds accruing thereto to be expended only for the purpose for which
2829 such funds are made available.
